# This function calls Chicago geometric from census package and picks only 
# tracts of Cook's county which are within the limits of city of Chicago
chicago_tracts <- function() {
  chicago <- get_acs(geography = "tract", 
                     variables = "B19013_001", 
                     state = "IL", 
                     county = c("Cook"), 
                     geometry = T)
  
  chicago_tracts <- read.csv("/Users/taiebat/Desktop/CensusTractsTIGER2010.csv")
  needed<-which(chicago$GEOID %in% chicago_tracts$GEOID10)    
  chicago <- chicago[needed,]
  return(chicago)
}
chicago <- chicago_tracts()

# Plot tax change per-trip, by census tract pick up and drop off
pickups <- data %>% 
  group_by(GEOID = pickup_census_tract) %>% 
  summarise("tax_change" = mean(tax_change, na.rm = T)) %>% 
  mutate(GEOID = as.character(GEOID))

vec <- c(-0.15, 0, 0.25, 0.35, 0.4, 0.45, 0.5, 0.55, 0.65, 0.75, 1, 1.25, 1.5, 1.75, 2.3)
lab <- c("below 0","0 to 0.25", "0.25 to 0.35", "0.35 to 0.4", 
         "0.4 to 0.45", "0.45 to 0.5", "0.5 to 0.55",  
         "0.55 to 0.65", "0.65 to 0.75",  "0.75 to 1", 
         "1 to 1.25", "1.25 to 1.5", "1.5 to 1.75", "above 1.75")
pickups$tax_change_cut <- cut(pickups$tax_change , breaks=vec, labels =lab)



chicago_pickups <- left_join(chicago, pickups, by = "GEOID")
chicago_pickups %>%
  filter(!is.na(tax_change_cut)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(fill = tax_change_cut)) + 
  geom_sf(color = NA) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  labs(fill = "Tax Change ($)" , 
       title = "Average Per-Trip Tax Change",
       subtitle = "By Pick Up Census Tract") +
  scale_fill_viridis_d(direction = 1, limits = rev(lab))

# Alternative Color Palette
# colors <- rev(RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(length(lab), "Spectral")) #also  RdYlBu
# scale_fill_manual(name = "Tax Change", 
#                     values = setNames(colors, lab), 
#                     breaks=rev(lab),
# =                   # guide=guide_legend(label.vjust=1.2),
#                     na.value="black")


dropoffs <- data  %>% 
  group_by(GEOID = dropoff_census_tract) %>% 
  summarise("tax_change" = mean(tax_change, na.rm = T)) %>% 
  mutate(GEOID = as.character(GEOID))
dropoffs$tax_change_cut <- cut(dropoffs$tax_change , breaks=vec, labels =lab)

chicago_dropoffs <- left_join(chicago, dropoffs, by = "GEOID")
chicago_dropoffs %>%
  filter(!is.na(tax_change_cut)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(fill = tax_change_cut)) + 
  geom_sf(color = NA) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  labs(fill = "Tax Change ($)" , 
       title = "Average Per-Trip Tax Change",
       subtitle = "By Drop Off Census Tract") +
  scale_fill_viridis_d(direction = 1, limits = rev(lab))

##### Maps for percentage change of fare+surchange under new policy 

data <- data %>% 
  mutate( "cost_change_pct" = tax_change * 100 / (fare + additional_charges) )

# by pick up tract
pickups <- data  %>% 
  group_by(GEOID = pickup_census_tract) %>% 
  summarise("cost_change_pct_mean" = mean( cost_change_pct , na.rm = T),
            "cost_change_pct_median" = median( cost_change_pct , na.rm = T)) %>% 
  mutate(GEOID = as.character(GEOID))

vec <- c(-1,0,2,3,3.5,4,4.5,5,6,8,10,12,16)
lab <- c("below 0","0 to 2", "2 to 3", "3 to 3.5", 
         "3.5 to 4", "4 to 4.5", "4.5 to 5",  
         "5 to 6", "6 to 8",  "8 to 10", 
         "10 to 12", "above 12")

pickups$cost_change_pct_mean_cut <- cut(pickups$cost_change_pct_mean , breaks=vec, labels =lab)
pickups$cost_change_pct_median_cut <- cut(pickups$cost_change_pct_median , breaks=vec, labels =lab)

chicago_pickups <- left_join(chicago, pickups, by = "GEOID")
chicago_pickups %>%
  filter(!is.na(cost_change_pct_mean_cut)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(fill = cost_change_pct_mean_cut)) + 
  geom_sf(color = NA) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  labs(fill = "Average Change\nin Trip Cost (%)" , 
       title = "Average Per-Trip Cost Change After Policy",
       subtitle = "By Pick Up Census Tract") +
  scale_fill_viridis_d(direction = 1, limits = rev(lab))

chicago_pickups %>%
  filter(!is.na(cost_change_pct_median_cut)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(fill = cost_change_pct_median_cut)) + 
  geom_sf(color = NA) + 
  theme_bw() + 
  labs(fill = "Median Change\nin Trip Cost (%)" , 
       title = "Median Per-Trip Cost Change After Policy",
       subtitle = "By Pick Up Census Tract") +
  scale_fill_viridis_d(direction = 1, limits = rev(lab))

# by drop off tract
dropoffs <- data  %>% 
  group_by(GEOID = dropoff_census_tract) %>% 
  summarise("cost_change_pct_mean" = mean( cost_change_pct , na.rm = T),
            "cost_change_pct_median" = median( cost_change_pct , na.rm = T)) %>% 
  mutate(GEOID = as.character(GEOID))

vec <- c(-1,0,2,3,3.5,4,4.5,5,6,8,10,12,16)
lab <- c("below 0","0 to 2", "2 to 3", "3 to 3.5", 
         "3.5 to 4", "4 to 4.5", "4.5 to 5",  
         "5 to 6", "6 to 8",  "8 to 10", 
         "10 to 12", "above 12")

dropoffs$cost_change_pct_mean_cut <- cut(dropoffs$cost_change_pct_mean , breaks=vec, labels =lab)
dropoffs$cost_change_pct_median_cut <- cut(dropoffs$cost_change_pct_median , breaks=vec, labels =lab)

chicago_dropoffs <- left_join(chicago, dropoffs, by = "GEOID")
